A worker came to fix the kitchen floor, and I pretended that I was just working from home, while in reality, I was editing "Hooked."
If only this damn file would open. (OneDrive is really crap.)
The hacker's voice: I'm in.
He started drilling, and the noise was huge. Great!
Turn the air purifier to the highest setting, and it feels a bit too intense for comfort, but I did indeed smell wood chips, so that justification holds. Moreover, he even opposes wearing masks. And I do need to protect myself, don't I?
I really want to go back to sleep, but I can only do that after he leaves.
The good news is that the fourth chapter is finally edited!
Chapter Five is very long and extremely anxiety-inducing. Yay! It's really thrilling.
Searching and replacing...➡️..., this chapter has 54 in total😅
But I still insist on this point: most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally agitated.
The floor repairman is using a vacuum cleaner to clean up, hoping that this means he is almost finished.
He went out (seeming to be cutting something). I sneakily glanced at the progress; there's still a lot left to do :(
Chapter 5 has 7 pages left. This remains my favorite chapter, and the manuscript is in fairly good shape, mainly with adjustments in formatting, as well as some minor tweaks to active voice and conciseness. But I really need a break and a cup of tea, and that guy is still fiddling around in my kitchen.
He started using the vacuum cleaner again. Fingers crossed that this is a good omen.
The worker who was fixing the kitchen floor has left!
He told me that he had quoted the full price for repairing the entire floor, but the landlord is very tight-fisted and only agreed to pay for repairing the section that was already rotten at the entrance. That feels much better.
I was drinking tea in the garden, while the air purifier in the kitchen was working hard to purify the room's air!
